<objectXMLWrap>
               <did xmlns="urn:isbn:1-931666-22-9">
                  <origination>
                     <persname>

Kirk, Andy, 1898-1992
</persname>
                  </origination>
                  <unittitle>

Andy Kirk papers 
<unitdate>

1923-1991
</unitdate>
                     <unitdate>

1935-1950
</unitdate>
                  </unittitle>
                  <physdesc>
                     <extent>

1.75 linear feet
</extent>
                  </physdesc>
                  <unitid>

2010210 Aa 2
</unitid>
                  <langmaterial>The material is in <language>English</language>
                  </langmaterial>
                  <abstract>

African American musician and bandleader Andy Kirk began a career that spanned more than thirty years in 1919, when he joined the George Morrison Orchestra as a saxophonist. He went on to earn renown as a bandleader and musician within the Big Band and Jazz genres.  The Andy Kirk papers include photographs, newspaper clippings, correspondence, and the rough draft manuscript for his autobiography <title>20 Years on Wheels</title> .
</abstract>
                  <repository>
                     <corpname>
                        <subarea>Bentley Historical Library</subarea>, University of Michigan</corpname>
                     <extptr/>
                  </repository>
               </did>
            </objectXMLWrap>
resource.title: Andy Kirk papers 1923-1991 1935-1950
resource.abstract: African American musician and bandleader Andy Kirk began a career that spanned more than thirty years in 1919, when he joined the George Morrison Orchestra as a saxophonist. He went on to earn renown as a bandleader and musician within the Big Band and Jazz genres.  The Andy Kirk papers include photographs, newspaper clippings, correspondence, and the rough draft manuscript for his autobiography . 20 Years on Wheels
